Two vehicles collided and burst into flames blocking the flow of traffic along the route for several hours. JOHANNESBURG - The N3 highway in Harrismith in the Free State has been reopened after a truck accident that left three people dead.A truck and a vehicle collided in the early hours of Friday and burst into flames blocking the flow of traffic along the route for several hours.Traffic spokesperson in the province Kabelo Moloabi said: The accident scene has been cleared and vehicles can travel smoothly. We are still experiencing a high volume of vehicles. (Edited by Winnie Theletsane)